  "intent_precise": "Nextera DNA Flex NGS Library Prep: Amplify Tagmented DNA: Using mag_plate (pcr_plate, slot 1), tubeblock (labware, slot 4), mastermix plate on chilled aluminum block (plate, slot 3). With magnetic module, temperature module. (1) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (2) Engage magnets at 18mm height for bead separation. (3) Transfer from reagent A1 to destination A1. (4) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (5) Transfer 120\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (6) Disengage magnets to release beads. (7) Transfer 40\u00b5L from mm A1 to destination. (8) Mix 10 times at 30\u00b5L. (9) Transfer 10\u00b5L from mm (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (10) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source to destination. (11) Mix 10 times at 20\u00b5L.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (4\u00b0C). (volumes 10\u00b5L-120\u00b5L)",
  "intent": "For the Nextera DNA Flex NGS Library Prep amplification step, start by setting up your magnetic plate in slot 1, tubeblock in slot 4, and mastermix plate on the chilled aluminum block in slot 3, then set the temperature module to 4\u00b0C and engage the magnetic module at 18mm height for bead separation. Transfer 50\u00b5L from reagent source A1 to destination A1, followed by 120\u00b5L from the same wells, then disengage the magnets and add 40\u00b5L from mastermix A1 to the destination, mixing 10 times at 30\u00b5L volume. Next, transfer 10\u00b5L from mastermix A1 to destination A1, add another 40\u00b5L transfer from source to destination, and finish with 10 more mixing cycles at 20\u00b5L volume to ensure proper incorporation of the amplification reagents.",
